Police in Ndhiwa are looking for a 26-year-old man who attacked and injured his parents and a sister at Ombasa village in Kwambwai ward. Pancras Ouma disappeared into a sugarcane plantation. The Monday incident started when Ouma got annoyed after a domestic quarrel ensued between him and the sister. The parents quarrelled with the man due to the squabbles. Neighbours said Ouma got annoyed, wrestled down his father before he picked a panga and slashed his arms. The suspect used the same weapon to attack his mother and the sister. West Kwabwai location senior chief Joseph Otieno Makoteng’ said the suspect seriously injured his three family members during the attack. He said the man slashed one of his mother’s thighs. The suspect is said to have intended to kill his family after he differed with his sister over an unclear reason. Residents started searching for the suspect. On Tuesday, a team of youths who accompanied chief Makoteng launched a manhunt for the suspect to arrest him but the man ambushed one youth and slashed his finger. The senior chief said the suspect spotted the youth and attacked him before he could call colleagues to come and arrest him. The youth (fourth victim) had his two fingers chopped off. Makoteng said the suspect disappeared when they took the attacked youth to the hospital. Those who were injured during the ordeal are receiving treatment at the Ndhiwa Subcounty Hospital. Ndhiwa Directorate of Criminal Investigation officers Paul Makonge said security officers are looking for the man who has made residents live in fear. By Wednesday morning the suspect had not been found. Edited by Kiilu Damaris